trans-unit.source: Represents an event that an instance store raises to notify hosts about a condition.
Examples: <xref href="System.Activities.DurableInstancing.HasRunnableWorkflowEvent"></xref> and <xref href="System.Activities.DurableInstancing.HasActivatableWorkflowEvent"></xref>.

Determines whether the current <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> object and the passed object converted as the <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> are the same.
The object to be compared with the current object.
Returns `True` if the objects are same; otherwise, returns `False`.

Determines whether the current <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> object and the passed <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> object are the same.
The object to be compared with the current object.
Returns `True` if the objects are same; otherwise, returns `False`.
Returns the hash code for the <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> instance.
The hash code for the instance.
Returns the XName (namespace combined with name) of the persistence event.
XName of the persistence event
Returns a value indicating whether the specified <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> objects are the same.
The first <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> object to compare.
The second <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> object to compare.
`True` if the two objects are the same; otherwise, `False`.
Returns a value indicating whether the specified <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> objects are not the same.
The first <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> object to compare.
The second <xref href="System.Runtime.DurableInstancing.InstancePersistenceEvent"></xref> object to compare.
`True` if the two objects are the same; otherwise, `False`.
